Function signature
String.prototype.codePointAt(pos) -> Number | undefined
Behavior (precise)
- Let i = ToInteger(pos).
- If i < 0 or i >= the length of the string (number of UTF-16 code units), return undefined.
- Let first = code unit at index i (a 16-bit value).
- If first is a high surrogate (0xD800..0xDBFF) and i+1 < length and the code unit at i+1 is a low surrogate (0xDC00..0xDFFF), return the combined code point:
  codePoint = ((first - 0xD800) << 10) + (second - 0xDC00) + 0x10000
- Otherwise return first.
Notes
- The return type is a Number in the range 0..0x10FFFF or undefined for out-of-range positions.
- The method does not normalize grapheme clusters; it decodes UTF-16 surrogate pairs into a single Unicode code point.
- Does not throw for non-integer or out-of-range pos; it returns undefined when pos is out-of-range after conversion to integer.
